  <md:title>Ownership of Capital</md:title>
  <md:abstract>When people think of Karl Marx they usually think of two things. One the injustice of inequality and standards of living, and two, the necessity of lessening inequality by taking wealth from some people and redistributing it to other people. But that's only half right. In this video, Professor Dan Russell explains that Karl Marx did not believe in wealth redistribution and explains what he advocated for instead.</md:abstract>
